|align=right}}
[[河狸科|河狸科]]属于[[啮齿目|啮齿目]]下的{{Le|河狸亚目|Castorimorpha}}，这个亚目还包括了[[異鼠科|异鼠科]]和[[囊鼠科|囊鼠科]]。如今河狸科下仅存一个河狸属，其余的属均已灭绝。河狸科起源于[[始新世|始新世]]的北美洲，在3300万年前的[[始新世-渐新世灭绝事件|始新世-渐新世灭绝事件]]时期通过[[白令陸橋|白令陆桥]]分散到欧亚大陆。<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Doronina |first=Liliya |last2=Matzke |first2=Andreas |last3=Churakov |first3=Gennady |last4=Stoll |first4=Monika |last5=Huge |first5=Andreas |last6=Schmitz |first6=Jürgen |date=2017-03-03 |title=The Beaver’s Phylogenetic Lineage Illuminated by Retroposon Reads |url=https://www.nature.com/articles/srep43562 |journal=Scientific Reports |language=en |volume=7 |issue=1 |doi=10.1038/srep43562 |issn=2045-2322 |pmc=PMC5335264 |pmid=28256552}}</ref><ref name="#1">{{Cite journal |last=Korth |first=William W. |date=2001-12-01 |title=Comments on the Systematics and Classification of the Beavers (Rodentia, Castoridae) |url=https://doi.org/10.1023/A:1014468732231 |journal=Journal of Mammalian Evolution |language=en |volume=8 |issue=4 |doi=10.1023/A:1014468732231 |issn=1573-7055}}</ref>

河狸[[基群|基群]]的特征包括：更加复杂的{{Le|颊齿|Cheek teeth}}[[咬合|咬合]]方式，平行排列的上排牙齿，[[前臼齒|前臼齿]]的尺寸与[[大臼齿|大臼齿]]相当，存在有第三对前臼齿，{{Le|镫骨肌|Stapedius muscle}}，光滑的[[腭骨|腭骨]]，腭孔（开口）更靠近骨骼的后端，并且有一个较长的[[吻突|鼻子]]。偏离河狸基群的成员则有着更简单的颊齿咬合方式，上排牙齿间距向后扩大，第二颗前臼齿尺寸大于大臼齿，没有第三对前臼齿，腭骨有凹槽，腭孔靠前。[[古河狸亚科|古河狸亚科]]（Palaeocastorinae ）起源于渐新世晚期的北美洲，这个亚科中的成员体型较小，适应挖掘洞穴的生活方式，它们的前肢相对较发达，头骨更低、更宽，尾巴更短。<ref name="#1"/>

大约在2400万年前的[[中新世|中新世]]早期，河狸演化出了{{Le|半水生|Semiaquatic}}的生活方式。也是在这个时期，河狸亚科出现了较大体型的成员，例如北美的[[巨河狸屬|巨河狸属]]和欧亚的[[大河狸|大河狸属]]。相比现代河狸，这些巨型河狸的水生程度较低。<ref name="#2">{{Cite journal |last=Rybczynski |first=Natalia |date=2007-03-01 |title=Castorid Phylogenetics: Implications for the Evolution of Swimming and Tree-Exploitation in Beavers |url=https://doi.org/10.1007/s10914-006-9017-3 |journal=Journal of Mammalian Evolution |language=en |volume=14 |issue=1 |doi=10.1007/s10914-006-9017-3 |issn=1573-7055}}</ref><ref name="#1"/> 巨河狸属的体长约为1.9-2.2米，体重为90-125千克。<ref>Swinehart, A. L.; Richards, R. L. (2001). "[https://journals.iupui.edu/index.php/ias/article/download/7219/7239 Paleoecology of Northeast Indiana Wetland Harboring Remains of the Pleistocene Giant Beaver (Castoroides Ohioensis)]". ''Proceedings of the Indiana Academy of Science''. '''110''': 151. Retrieved November 21, 2014.</ref> 曾在被啃咬的树木旁发现已灭绝的{{Le|假河狸属|Dipoides}}的化石遗迹，尽管相比现代河狸，它们的伐木技能并不算高。有科学家主张，现代河狸和{{Le|拟河狸亚科|Castoroidinae}}有一个以树皮为食的[[最近共同祖先|共同祖先]]。<ref name="#3">{{Cite journal |last=Plint |first=Tessa |last2=Longstaffe |first2=Fred J. |last3=Ballantyne |first3=Ashley |last4=Telka |first4=Alice |last5=Rybczynski |first5=Natalia |date=2020-08-04 |title=Evolution of woodcutting behaviour in Early Pliocene beaver driven by consumption of woody plants |url=https://www.nature.com/articles/s41598-020-70164-1 |journal=Scientific Reports |language=en |volume=10 |issue=1 |doi=10.1038/s41598-020-70164-1 |issn=2045-2322 |pmc=PMC7403313 |pmid=32753594}}</ref> 筑造水坝和木屋的技能可能来自吃树皮的习惯，这可以帮助河狸度过高纬度的严酷寒冬。<ref name="#2"/> 在现代河狸以外的物种中尚未发现类似行为的确凿证据。<ref name="#3"/>

现代河狸可能起源于欧亚大陆，其中最古老的化石遗骸似乎是来自德国的 C. neglectus，时间大约在1200-1000万年前。<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Samuels |first=Joshua X. |last2=Zancanella |first2=John |date=2011-09 |title=An Early Hemphillian Occurrence of Castor (Castoridae) from the Rattlesnake Formation of Oregon |url=https://bioone.org/journals/journal-of-paleontology/volume-85/issue-5/11-016.1/An-Early-Hemphillian-Occurrence-of-Castor-Castoridae-from-the-Rattlesnake/10.1666/11-016.1.full |journal=Journal of Paleontology |volume=85 |issue=5 |doi=10.1666/11-016.1 |issn=0022-3360}}</ref> 生活在北美的现代河狸可能是在[[中新世|中新世]]后期通过[[白令陸橋|白令陆桥]]迁徙过去的。通过对[[线粒体DNA|线粒体DNA]]的研究显示，北美河狸与欧亚河狸大约在800万年前分离。<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Horn |first=Susanne |last2=Durka |first2=Walter |last3=Wolf |first3=Ronny |last4=Ermala |first4=Aslak |last5=Stubbe |first5=Annegret |last6=Stubbe |first6=Michael |last7=Hofreiter |first7=Michael |date=2011-01-28 |title=Mitochondrial Genomes Reveal Slow Rates of Molecular Evolution and the Timing of Speciation in Beavers (Castor), One of the Largest Rodent Species |url=https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0014622 |journal=PLOS ONE |language=en |volume=6 |issue=1 |doi=10.1371/journal.pone.0014622 |issn=1932-6203 |pmc=PMC3030560 |pmid=21307956}}</ref> 现代河狸可能在与{{Le|拟河狸亚科|Castoroidinae}}的竞争过程中出现了{{Le|生态位分化|Niche differentiation}}。<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Samuels |first=Joshua X. |last2=Van Valkenburgh |first2=Blaire |date=2008-11 |title=Skeletal indicators of locomotor adaptations in living and extinct rodents |url=https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/jmor.10662 |journal=Journal of Morphology |language=en |volume=269 |issue=11 |doi=10.1002/jmor.10662}}</ref> 欧亚河狸的祖先可能是 C. praefiber。<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Barisone |first=Giancarlo |last2=Argenti |first2=Patrizia |last3=Kotsakis |first3=Tassos |date=2006-11-01 |title=Plio-Pleistocene evolution of the genus Castor (Rodentia, Mammalia) in Europe: C. fiber plicidens of Pietrafitta (Perugia, Central Italy) |url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0016699506000684 |journal=Geobios |language=en |volume=39 |issue=6 |doi=10.1016/j.geobios.2005.10.004 |issn=0016-6995}}</ref> 出现在{{Le|早更新世|Early Pleistocene}}北美洲的{{Le|加州河狸|Castor californicus}}外形与现存的北美河狸相似，但体型更大。<ref>{{Cite book|chapter=|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/5830693|publisher=Columbia University Press|date=1980|location=New York|isbn=0-231-03733-3|oclc=5830693|first=Elaine|last=Anderson|title=Pleistocene mammals of North America}}</ref>

== 特征 ==
[[File:Beaver_skeleton.jpg|thumb]][[奧克拉荷馬州|奧克拉荷馬州]][[骨骼博物馆|骨骼博物館]]）|左]]河狸在现存的啮齿类动物有第二大的体型，仅次于[[水豚属|水豚]]。它们的头-身长度在80-120厘米，尾巴长度25-50厘米，肩高30-60厘米，体重11-30千克。<ref name=":2">{{Cite book|chapter=|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/48048972|publisher=Barnes & Noble Books|date=2001|location=New York|isbn=0-7607-1969-1|oclc=48048972|first=David W.|last=Macdonald|title=The encyclopedia of mammals}}</ref> 雌雄个体的外观几乎一致。{{sfn|Müller-Schwarze|Sun|2003|p=14}} 它们的身体呈现出与海洋哺乳动物类似的流线形，强壮的身体有利于承受重物。<ref name=":3">{{Cite book|edition=2nd ed|chapter=|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/51969059|publisher=Johns Hopkins University Press|date=2003|location=Baltimore, Md.|isbn=0-8018-7416-5|oclc=51969059|first=George A.|last=Feldhamer|first2=Bruce Carlyle|last2=Thompson|first3=Joseph A.|last3=Chapman|title=Wild mammals of North America : biology, management, and conservation}}</ref>{{Sfn|Runtz|2015|p=73}} 河狸的毛发密度为12,000-23,000根/平方厘米，毛发主要用于保暖，增加在水中的浮力，并减少被捕食者咬伤的风险。它们的毛发长度在5-6厘米，一般为红棕色，但也可能偏向黄棕色或几近黑色。毛发延伸到皮肤下2-3厘米，皮下毛发为深棕色。河狸会在夏天[[蜕皮|蜕皮]]。<ref name=":2" />{{sfn|Müller-Schwarze|Sun|2003|p=12}}

河狸演化出了巨大的头骨，用于承受咀嚼肌的强大咬合力。它们有4个不断生长的[[鑿|凿]]形门牙，因为其中含有铁合物，门牙的外釉质很厚并呈橙色。{{sfn|Müller-Schwarze|Sun|2003|pp=11-12}}<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Gordon |first=Lyle M. |last2=Cohen |first2=Michael J. |last3=MacRenaris |first3=Keith W. |last4=Pasteris |first4=Jill D. |last5=Seda |first5=Takele |last6=Joester |first6=Derk |date=2015-02-13 |title=Amorphous intergranular phases control the properties of rodent tooth enamel |url=https://www.science.org/doi/10.1126/science.1258950 |journal=Science |language=en |volume=347 |issue=6223 |doi=10.1126/science.1258950 |issn=0036-8075}}</ref>下门牙的根部一直延伸到下颌底。河狸的上下颌各有一颗[[前臼齒|前臼齿]]和三颗[[大臼齿|大臼齿]]，总共有20颗牙齿。臼齿上有脊，便于研磨木质食物。{{sfn|Müller-Schwarze|Sun|2003|p=12}}河狸的眼睛、耳朵和鼻孔有特定的排列方式，当身体的其余部分淹没时，这些器官可以保持在水面之上。当位于水底时，河狸鼻孔和耳朵的中的阀门可以主动关闭，[[瞬膜|瞬膜]]覆盖眼睛。与其它哺乳动物不同的是，河狸的[[会厌|会厌]]包含在鼻腔而不是喉咙中，以防水流入[[喉|喉部]]和[[氣管|气管]]。此外，舌头根部也可抬升以防止水的流入。河狸的嘴唇可以门牙后面闭合，这允许它们在水中咀嚼食物。{{Sfn|Runtz|2015|p=55}}<ref>{{Cite book|chapter=|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/908671607|publisher=Pelagic Publishing|date=2015|location=Exeter|isbn=978-1-78427-040-7|oclc=908671607|first=Derek|last=Gow|first2=Robert|last2=Needham|first3=Simon|last3=Jones|first4=Frank|last4=Rosell|title=The Eurasian Beaver.}}</ref>

河狸的前肢十分灵巧，这允许它们方便的抓取食物和挖掘洞穴。河狸的后脚有[[蹼|蹼]]，后足第二趾有双趾甲。<ref name=":4">{{Cite book|chapter=|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/908671607|publisher=Pelagic Publishing|date=2015|location=Exeter|isbn=978-1-78427-040-7|oclc=908671607|first=Derek|last=Gow|first2=Robert|last2=Needham|first3=Simon|last3=Jones|first4=Frank|last4=Rosell|title=The Eurasian Beaver.}}</ref>{{sfn|Runtz|2015|p=71}} 他们的游泳速度为 8 km/h{{sfn|Runtz|2015|p=73}}，游泳时只用到后肢，前肢蜷缩在胸前。<ref name=":4" /> 浮在水面时，河狸的后肢交错推动，潜水时，后肢同步移动。<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Allers |first=Dirk |last2=Culik |first2=Boris M. |date=1997-07-01 |title=Energy Requirements of Beavers (Castor canadensis) Swimming Underwater |url=https://www.journals.uchicago.edu/doi/10.1086/515852 |journal=Physiological Zoology |volume=70 |issue=4 |doi=10.1086/515852 |issn=0031-935X}}</ref> 河狸在陆地上行动比较笨拙，但在遇到危险时仍可快速移动。当它们使用后肢行走时，前肢可以携带物品。<ref name=":3" /><ref name=":4" />

== 习性 ==
[[File:American_Beaver,_tree_cutting.jpg|thumb]]
[[File:Picture_Natural_History_-_No_40_41_42_-_Beaver_feet_and_tail.png|thumb]]
河狸會在河流或溪流中利用樹枝、草和泥巴構築水壩，形成池塘，並在池塘中建立巢穴（又稱為小屋（{{lang-en|lodge}}））；同時也會建造運河來運輸巢穴與水壩的建材<ref name="Salvesen">{{cite journal|last1=Salvesen|first1=Sigvald|title=The Beaver in Norway |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-mammalogy_1928-05_9_2/page/99|date=May 1928|pages=99–104 |doi=10.2307/1373424|volume=9|issue=2|journal=Journal of Mammalogy|jstor=1373424}}<!--|accessdate=2 April 2015--></ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animaltrial.com/beaver/beaverdamandcanals.html|title=Beaver Dams and Canals|publisher=animaltrail|accessdate=2013-06-26|archive-date=2013-05-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130526192829/http://www.animaltrial.com/beaver/beaverdamandcanals.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。牠們會用鋒利的[[門牙|門牙]]咬斷樹木與其他植物作為建材以及食物。

[[File:Beaverbones.jpg|thumb]]

當發現潛在的威脅時，在水中的河狸會用力拍擊水面，警告範圍內的所有河狸。在聽到警告聲後，所有河狸都會躲入水中，牠們在陸地上時雖然行動緩慢，卻很擅長游泳，而且可以憋氣長達 15 分鐘。

河狸並不[[冬眠|冬眠]]，而是會將樹枝和樹幹堆放在池塘中，做為儲糧。

河狸的後腳有蹼、並且具有寬扁的尾巴。視力不好，但聽覺、嗅覺和觸覺敏銳。牠們必須透過不斷啃咬木頭來防止門牙變得過長<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.beaversolutions.com/about_beaver_biology.asp |title=Beaver Biology |publisher=Beaver Solutions |accessdate=2010-03-15 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100414110435/http://www.beaversolutions.com/about_beaver_biology.asp |archivedate=2010-04-14 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。牠們的四顆[[門牙|門牙]]由前側堅硬的[[琺瑯質|琺瑯質]]以及背側較柔軟的[[牙本質|牙本質]]所組成，透過啃咬木頭的方式將門牙磨利成[[鑿|鑿]]狀。河狸門牙中上的琺瑯質含有[[鐵|鐵]]，比起其他[[哺乳動物|哺乳動物]]的門牙更能抵抗酸蝕<ref name=NW>{{cite web|author1=Megan Fellman|title=Making Teeth Tough: Beavers Show Way To Improve Our Enamel (Discovery could lead to better understanding of tooth decay process, early detection)|url=http://www.northwestern.edu/newscenter/stories/2015/02/making-teeth-tough-beavers-show-way-to-improve-our-enamel-.html|website=www.northwestern.edu|accessdate=2015-02-19|date=2015-02-12|archive-date=2016-07-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160729010557/http://www.northwestern.edu/newscenter/stories/2015/02/making-teeth-tough-beavers-show-way-to-improve-our-enamel-.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

河狸終其一生不斷成長，成年體重可以超過 {{convert|25|kg|lb|abbr=on}}，雌性一般較雄性大。在野外壽命可長達 24 年。

==栖息地==
[[File:Beaver_Dam.jpg|thumb]]，也就是溪流與陸地的交界處]]
河狸主要棲息於[[河岸濕地|河岸濕地]]，包括溪床。但也有部分河狸棲息於[[潮間帶|潮間帶]]，構築水壩將漲潮時帶進來的海水留在構築出的池塘中<ref>{{cite news |last1=Goldfarb |first1=Ben |title=The Gnawing Question of Saltwater Beavers |url=https://www.hakaimagazine.com/features/the-gnawing-question-of-saltwater-beavers/ |accessdate=2019-02-01 |work=[[Hakai_magazine|Hakai magazine]] |date=2019-01-29 |archive-date=2019-11-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191130183921/https://www.hakaimagazine.com/features/the-gnawing-question-of-saltwater-beavers/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Hood |first1=W. Gregory |title=Beaver in Tidal Marshes: Dam Effects on Low-Tide Channel Pools and Fish Use of Estuarine Habitat |journal=Wetlands |volume=32 |issue=3 |pages=401–410 |date=2012-02-16 |doi=10.1007/s13157-012-0294-8 |url=https://beaverinstitute.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/TidalMarshBeavers2012.pdf |accessdate=2019-02-01 |archive-date=2020-04-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200409235500/https://beaverinstitute.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/TidalMarshBeavers2012.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

河狸為[[生態系統|生態系統]]的[[關鍵種|關鍵種]]，創造[[濕地|濕地]]供其他物種生存。研究发现，河狸创造的湿地与普通的湿地相比，有更充足的食物。因此，河狸创造的湿地对一些水鸟和哺乳动物来说是很好的栖息地<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Nummi|first1=P.|last2=Liao|first2=W.|last3=Huet|first3=O.|last4=Scarpulla|first4=E.|last5=Sundell|first5=J.|title=The beaver facilitates species richness and abundance of terrestrial and semi-aquatic mammals|journal=Global Ecology and Conservation|year=2019|doi=10.1016/j.gecco.2019.e00701|volume=20}}</ref>。河狸為僅次於人類，最有能力塑造地表的動物<ref>{{cite web |title=Beaver (beavers 'second only to humans in their ability to manipulate and change their environment') |work=[[National_Geographic|National Geographic]] |accessdate=2009-06-15 |url=http://animals.nationalgeographic.com/animals/mammals/beaver.html |archive-date=2011-07-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110723141310/http://animals.nationalgeographic.com/animals/mammals/beaver.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，甚至會影響[[氣候變遷|氣候變遷]]<ref>{{cite journal|last=Wohl|first=Ellen|title=Landscape-scale carbon storage associated with Beaver Dams|journal=Geophysical Research Letters|year=2013|doi=10.1002/grl.50710|volume=40|issue=14|pages=3631–3636}}</ref>。

河狸會咬斷大顆的樹木作為水壩的基底，不過歐亞河狸則較傾向咬斷直徑{{convert|10|cm}}的樹木做為基底。較小棵的樹木則會被河狸咬斷作為食物。

被砍斷的樹木會萌芽長成矮林，提供給河狸接下來數年穩定的樹葉與嫩枝食物來源。河狸構築水壩所造成的池塘會淹死浸泡在其中的樹木，而這些死掉的樹木對於許多動物及植物的生存尤其重要<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://extension.psu.edu/natural-resources/wildlife/habitat-management/dead-wood-for-wildlife|title=Dead Wood for Wildlife (Wildlife Outreach Center)|website=Wildlife Outreach Center (Penn State Extension)|access-date=2016-09-23|archive-date=2016-09-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160924120636/http://extension.psu.edu/natural-resources/wildlife/habitat-management/dead-wood-for-wildlife|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===河狸水坝===
{{Multiple image
| direction = horizontal
| align = top
| header = 水坝扩大
| width1 = 250
| image1 = Beaver dam - geograph.org.uk - 1452003.jpg
| caption1 = 河狸水坝
| width2 = 250
| image2 = Beaver dam - four months on - geograph.org.uk - 1623430.jpg
| caption2 = 四个月后，变大了
}}
河狸建造水坝的主要目的是为了防范天敌，如土狼、狼、熊等，冬天时更容易获取食物。牠们总是在夜里开工，而且是高生產力的建筑师，用前爪搬运泥和石块，用牙搬运木料。不移除河狸的话，很难摧毁水坝，因为牠们隔夜就能重建一座水坝。河狸可能沿河建造一系列的水坝。

河狸建造水壩後形成的池塘與溼地可以留住水流中的沉積物與污染物，包括[[總懸浮固體|總懸浮固體]]、總氮、磷、碳及矽酸鹽<ref>{{cite journal |title=Beaver pond biogeochemical effects in the Maryland Coastal Plain |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_biogeochemistry_2000-06_49_3/page/217 |journal=Biogeochemistry |date=June 2000 |pages=217–239 |jstor=1469618 |author1=David L. Correll |author2=Thomas E. Jordan |author3=Donald E. Weller |volume=49 |issue=3 |doi=10.1023/a:1006330501887}}</ref><ref name=Muskopf>{{cite thesis |title=The Effect of Beaver (Castor canadensis) Dam Removal on Total Phosphorus Concentration in Taylor Creek and Wetland, South Lake Tahoe, California |author=Sarah Muskopf |publisher=Humboldt State University, Natural Resources |date=October 2007 |hdl=2148/264 }}</ref>。

[[File:Blaeu_-_Nova_Belgica_et_Anglia_Nova_(Detail_Hudson_Area).png|thumb]]谷地图上的河狸 c. 1635]]

== 生存现状 ==
河狸位于[[國際自然保護聯盟瀕危物種紅色名錄|IUCN红色名录]]中的[[无危物种|无危物种]]一列。<ref name=":5">{{Cite journal |last=IUCN |date=2016-08-07 |title=Castor canadensis: Cassola, F.: The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2016: e.T4003A22187946 |url=http://www.iucnredlist.org/details/4003/0 |language=en |doi=10.2305/iucn.uk.2016-3.rlts.t4003a22187946.en}}</ref><ref name=":6">[https://www.iucnredlist.org/species/4007/115067136 Eurasian Beaver]</ref> 北美河狸分布十分广泛，遍及美国和加拿大的大部分国土，在墨西哥北部也有它们的踪迹。北美河狸于1937年被引入芬兰（而后散播到了俄罗斯西北部），1946年被引入[[火地群岛|火地群岛]]。<ref>{{Cite journal |last=IUCN |date=2016-08-07 |title=Castor canadensis: Cassola, F.: The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2016: e.T4003A22187946 |url=http://www.iucnredlist.org/details/4003/0 |language=en |doi=10.2305/iucn.uk.2016-3.rlts.t4003a22187946.en}}</ref> 至2019年，芬兰境内的北美河狸种群数量已接近当地原生的欧亚河狸数量。<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Alakoski |first=Riikka |last2=Kauhala |first2=Kaarina |last3=Selonen |first3=Vesa |date=2019-05-01 |title=Differences in habitat use between the native Eurasian beaver and the invasive North American beaver in Finland |url=https://doi.org/10.1007/s10530-019-01919-9 |journal=Biological Invasions |language=en |volume=21 |issue=5 |doi=10.1007/s10530-019-01919-9 |issn=1573-1464}}</ref> 历史上，北美河狸曾因其皮毛价值而受到大量捕杀，使它们接近灭绝。在后续保护措施的帮助下，河狸种群数量持续回升，到20世纪末期达到了600至1200万，不过仍远少于大规模狩猎前6000万至4亿的规模。<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Naiman |first=Robert J. |last2=Johnston |first2=Carol A. |last3=Kelley |first3=James C. |date=1988-12-01 |title=Alteration of North American Streams by Beaver: The structure and dynamics of streams are changing as beaver recolonize their historic habitat |url=https://doi.org/10.2307/1310784 |journal=BioScience |volume=38 |issue=11 |doi=10.2307/1310784 |issn=0006-3568}}</ref> 根据2016年的估算，[[火地群岛|火地群岛]]的北美河狸数量大约在 35,000至50,000。<ref name=":5" />

欧亚河狸的栖息范围并不连续，而是被分为了多个[[生境破碎化|区块]]。欧亚河狸曾广泛分布于欧亚大陆，但20世纪初期的过度狩猎显著降低了它们的种群数量。在欧洲，欧亚河狸的族群曾被孤立为法国[[罗讷河|罗讷河]]、德国[[易北河|易北河]]、挪威南部、[[尼曼河|尼曼河]]、白俄罗斯[[第聂伯河|第聂伯河]]盆地、俄罗斯的[[沃羅涅日河|沃羅涅日河]]这些独立的区域，总数量估计在1,200。在后续的[[再引入|再引入]]的努力下，欧亚河狸返回了部分先前的栖息地。如今，欧亚河狸的种群从法国、西班牙横跨至中欧与东欧，一直到[[斯堪的纳维亚|斯堪的纳维亚]]和俄罗斯。<ref name=":6" /> 自2009年起，河狸被成功的引入了英国。<ref>{{Cite web |title=Beaver Reintroduction in the UK |url=https://www.rspb.org.uk/our-work/policy-insight/species/beaver-reintroduction-in-the-uk/ |website=The RSPB |language=en-GB |access-date=2022-06-13}}</ref> 根据2020年的估算，欧洲大约有超过100万只河狸。<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Wróbel |first=Michał |date=2020-09-01 |title=Population of Eurasian beaver (Castor fiber) in Europe |url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S2351989420302456 |journal=Global Ecology and Conservation |language=en |volume=23 |doi=10.1016/j.gecco.2020.e01046 |issn=2351-9894}}</ref> 在蒙古和中国的西北部也生活着本地小型族群，根据2016年的估算，这些种群数量分别在150和700左右。<ref name=":6" /> 根据新西兰的《{{Le|1996 年有害物质和外来生物法案|Hazardous Substances and New Organisms Act 1996}}》，河狸被禁止引入该国。<ref>{{Cite web |title=Hazardous Substances and New Organisms Act 1996 No 30 (as at 12 April 2022), Public Act Schedule 2 Prohibited new organisms – New Zealand Legislation |url=https://legislation.govt.nz/act/public/1996/0030/latest/DLM386556.html |website=legislation.govt.nz |access-date=2022-06-13}}</ref>

